      <title>New Multi-touch Interactions on the Apple iPad</title>
      <link>http://konigi.com/blog/new-multi-touch-interactions-apple-ipad/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 29 Jan 2010 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://konigi.com/blog/new-multi-touch-interactions-apple-ipad/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;notebook-screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.lukew.com/ff/entry.asp?991&#34;&gt;&lt;img id=&#39;bluga-thumbnail-2292&#39; class=&#39;bluga-thumbnail large&#39; src=&#39;http://media.konigi.com/bluga/
wt4b630611958c1_large.jpg&#39;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Craig Villamor and Luke Wroblewski summarize the new interactions we&amp;rsquo;ll be seeing in the iPad.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;During Apple&#39;s 90 minute unveiling of the iPad this week, a lot of new multi-touch interactions were shown off. But they went by fast. So as a service to digital product designers everywhere, we took the time to extract 8 minutes of new user interface demos from the iPad keynote. Now you can quickly just catch the UI in action on Apple&#39;s new native iPad and iWork applications.&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

